<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fa" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fa,</orth> the fourth note in the gamut: <cit><quote>ut, re, sol, la, mi, fa,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 102</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>C fa ut,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 1, 76</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fa, sol, la, mi,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 149</bibl></cit>. Used as a verb: <cit><quote>I'll try how you can sol, fa,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 17</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'll re you, I'll fa you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 4.5.121" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 5, 121</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>